### Explanation

- The program first reads all lines from `votes.txt` into memory.
- It separates candidate names from votes by checking if the line is an integer or not.
- Candidate names are stored in an array; votes are stored as integers.
- Votes are tallied, invalid votes identified and printed.
- The summary and candidate scores are printed.
- Winners (one or more) are identified and printed.

---

### Compile and run

```bash
gcc election.c -o election
./election
```

The results will be written to `resultats.txt`.

